title: 2021 MAXXD G8X G8X8322 Equipment Trailer
description: 2021 MAXXD Trailers G8X G8X8322Heavy Duty Features Simple Operation The G8X is the split deck gravity tilting version of our best-in-class T8X powered tilt trailer. The G8X tilt deck equipment trailer offers a hydraulically dampened tilting deck with your choice of a 4’ 6’ 8’ 10’ or 12’ stationary front deck. This gives you room to load cargo up front and still have the option to haul heavier equipment like tractors skid steers recreational vehicles and SUVs or cars. Available in 22’ 24’ 26’ 28’ and 30’ total lengths the G8X tilt deck equipment trailer comes standard with two 7K Dexter torsion electric brake axles for a standard GVRW of 14000 pounds. These torsion axles provide a smoother ride and a longer warranty than comparable spring axles as well as a lower overall ride height. Combined with the mechanically simple easy-to-tilt bed these lower axles make your G8X tilt deck equipment trailer safe and easy to load. A rugged knife-edge rear deck brings the back of the trailer all the way to the ground when the bed is tilted making it ideal for loading low-clearance equipment and vehicles. The diamond-plate steel edge provides enhanced durability for this high-wear area as well. The G8X also includes bullnose D-rings and a full-length stake pocket and rub rail system for plenty of options when tying down your vehicles. Like all MAXX-D trailers the G8X tilt deck equipment trailer is finished with our industry-leading powder coating process. Six different steps all work together to give your tilt trailer a premium powder-coated steel surface with unmatched durability. Through our expansive dealer network we give you the option to configure your G8X tilt deck equipment trailer with a variety of options to fit your needs. Whether it’s an extra set of D-rings flooring style coupler configuration or your choice of jack you can get a G8X that’s perfect for whatever it is you’re building. We build the G8X tilt deck equipment trailer in an 83” deck width or a 102” overall width with drive-over fenders in either gooseneck or bumper pull configurations. Build something great with the G5X gravity tilt equipment trailer!

title: 2022 MAXXD N6X N6X8320 Car / Racing Trailer
description: 2022 MAXXD Trailers N6X N6X8320High-End Style And Features The N6X is a premium choice if you need a user-friendly car hauler that works hard while looking good. A rugged tubular frame and enhanced features like running boards and aluminum trim make the N6X car trailer perfect for regularly hauling cars and trucks. The 72” ramps on the N6X are designed from the ground up with ease of use in mind. We designed the front part of the ramp to “stop” the ramp when removing it from the ramp pocket connecting it to the trailer. This easy-to-use design also provides an ideal loading angle and we give you the option to upgrade the standard dovetail to an attractive split design. Two Dexter 5200 lb axles come standard on the N5X for a 9990 lb GVWR. The N6X can be configured with a toolbox at the front of the trailer as well as an in-floor toolbox for tie-down and tool storage. The floor on the N6X car trailer is constructed from 1/8” diamond plate and offers flush-fitting D-rings as tie-downs. As an option full-length E-track is available on the N6X to give you virtually limitless options when tying down. Combined with some extra D-rings the E-track will let you haul practically any car. We build the N6X car hauling trailer in lengths ranging from 18’ to 24’ in two-foot increments with a standard width of 83”. Flush-mounted LED lighting and radial tires come standard on every N6X. Like all MAXX-D Trailers the N6X car hauler is finished with our industry-leading powder coating process. Six different steps all work together to give this trailer a premium powder-coated steel surface with unmatched durability. Through our expansive dealer network we give you the option to configure your N6X car hauling trailer with a variety of options to fit your needs. Whether it’s a winch plate front toolbox tie-down options or your choice of color you can get an N5X that’s perfect for whatever cars you’re hauling. We offer the N6X with 2” or 2 5/6” adjustable ball coupler options all with the premium components and dealer support you’ve come to expect from MAXX-D Trailers. Build something great with an N5X tubular frame car hauler!

title: 2021 MAXXD G6X G6X8324 Equipment Trailer
description: 2021 MAXXD Trailers G6X G6X8324The Best Of Both Worlds The G6X is the split deck gravity tilting version of our best-in-class T6X powered tilt trailer. The G6X gravity tilt trailer offers a hydraulically dampened tilting deck with your choice of a 4’ 6’ or 8’ stationary front deck. This gives you room to load cargo up front and still have the option to haul equipment like cars skid steers scissor lifts or small forklifts in the back. Available in 20’ 22’ and 24’ lengths the G6X gravity tilt car trailer comes standard with two 7K Dexter torsion electric brake axles for a GVRW of 14000 pounds. These torsion axles provide a smoother ride and a longer warranty than comparable spring axles as well as a lower overall ride height. Combined with the mechanically simple easy-to-tilt bed these lower axles make your G6X gravity tilt car trailer safe and easy to load. A rugged knife-edge rear deck brings the back of the trailer all the way to the ground when the bed is tilted making it ideal for loading low-clearance equipment like scissor lifts and lighter forklifts. The diamond-plate steel edge provides enhanced durability for this high-wear area as well. Like all MAXX-D trailers the G6X gravity tilt car trailer is finished with our industry-leading powder coating process. Six different steps all work together to give your tilt trailer a premium powder-coated steel surface with unmatched durability. Through our expansive dealer network we give you the option to configure your G6X gravity tilt trailer with a variety of options to fit your needs. Whether it’s an extra set of D-rings flooring style coupler configuration or your choice of jack you can get a G6X that’s perfect for whatever it is you’re building. We build the G6X gravity tilt trailer in an 83” deck width or a 102” overall width with drive-over fenders in either gooseneck or bumper pull configurations. Build something great with the G6X gravity tilt car trailer!

title: 2022 MAXXD DJX DJX8316 Dump Trailer
description: 2022 MAXXD Trailers DJX DJX8316A Configuration For Any Situation We offer an incredible amount of variety and customization in all the dump trailers we offer but the DJX takes it up a notch. It’s equally at home hauling loose brush loads or heavy equipment. Based on an 8” I-beam frame the DJX includes heavy-duty features like an industry-leading 6” scissor hoist. We house the KTI hydraulic pump and Interstate battery in a unique full-width internally split toolbox. This protects the heart of the hydraulics system and provides a convenient place for chains and other important tools. You can also choose to outfit the DJX with 2’ 3’ or 4’ tall Tuff Sides. These sides provide a massive 3” top cap surface that wraps partially down the side of the trailer. These top rails are then supported with flared steel side supports. Combined they help form a bed that’s extremely resistant to warping dents and damage. All of our dumps come equipped with tarp-kits as a standard feature. We build each DJX with a standard GVWR of 14000 lbs and twin 7K Dexter electric brake axles. You can configure these versatile dumps in lengths of 12’ 14' and 16' with base weights ranging from 4150 lbs to 4550 lbs. Like all MAXX-D Trailers the DJX I-beam dump model is finished with our industry-leading powder coating process. Six different steps all work together to give your trailer a premium powder-coated steel surface with unmatched durability. Through our expansive dealer network we give you the option to configure your DJX low profile dump trailer with a variety of options to fit your needs. Whether it’s an extra set of D-rings solar battery charger or your choice of side height and configuration you can get a DJX that’s perfect for whatever it is you’re building. With both gooseneck and bumper pull styles available the DJX is an ideal choice for construction roofing agriculture landscaping and any other large projects you can dream of. Build something great with a DJX I-beam dump trailer!

title: 2022 MAXXD TOX TOX10222 Flatbed Trailer
description: 2022 MAXXD Trailers TOX TOX10222Your Next Do-All Powered Tilt Trailer The TOX is ideal for general construction jobs equipment hauling car transport and just about anything else you can think of. The easily accessible bumper-pull design is perfect for tasks that require a compact trailer featuring plenty of hauling capacity. With a total trailer base weight of 4150 pounds (22’ model) you can haul up to 9850 pounds from jobsite to jobsite with ease. Twin hydraulic cylinders keep your load balanced and under control while raising and lowering the 22’ bed with the powered tilt system. A diamond plated knife edge on the rear of the deck makes loading low-clearance equipment easy while maintaining the durability real-world construction jobs demand. Twin 7k Dexter electric brake axles with slipper spring suspension come standard on the TOX deck over tilt deck trailer for a 14000 pound GVWR and are upgradable to electric/hydraulic brakes. 8k Dexter electric brake axles are also available for installation. Like all MAXX-D Trailers the TOX powered tilt deck trailer is finished with our industry-leading powder coating process. Six different preparation steps all work together to give your trailer a premium powder coated steel surface with unmatched durability. Through our expansive dealer network we give you the option to configure your TOX powered tilt deck trailer with a variety of options to fit your needs. Whether it’s an extra set of D-rings diamond plated steel floor coupler style or your choice of tires you can get a TOX that’s perfect for whatever it is you’re building. While the TOX excels in the standard I-beam tongue bumper pull configuration we also offer it in a variety of versatile gooseneck configurations as well. Build something great with the TOX powered tilt deck trailer!

title: 2023 MAXXD U4X U4X8318 Utility Trailer
description: 2023 MAXXD Trailers U4X U4X8318The Tandem Axle Utility Trailer That’S Up For The Challenge The U4X Tandem Axle Utility Trailer is a 9990 lbs GVWR medium-duty utility trailer that is great for hauling all kinds of things: Hauling your UTV’s and ATV’s lawn mowers materials or even a small tractor with your half ton or bigger truck. The U4X deck is 18’ long and 83 inches wide and has 11” tall sides topped with 2” square tubing and has stake pockets and and weighs 2700 lbs so it’s haulable with a half ton or bigger truck. The U4X has an 11” tall 2” square tubing top-rail on the front and sides of the trailer and has hooks on the bottom corners of the deck for easy tying down of cargo. Up front the U4X hooks to your vehicle with a 2 5/16” DEMCO EZ-Latch adjustable coupler mounted to a 5” channel wrap tongue and a 5” x 3” x ¼” steel angle mainframe. The treated wood floor deck is supported by 3” x 2” Angle crossmembers spaced at 16” apart. A 7k drop leg jack raises and lowers the front of the trailer. Two 5200 lb brake axles paired with 225/75 radial tires carry the U4X down the road and a heavy-duty spring-assisted 4’ tall steel mesh gate in the rear makes loading your stuff super simple and easy. Along with steel diamond plate fenders this trailer has clear LED running lights on the sides and in the rear bumper as well. Like all of our trailers the U4X is 100% built in Texas and is ready to get work done. We build trailers for the working man.

title: 2023 MAXXD U5X U5X8320 Utility Trailer
description: 2023 MAXXD Trailers U5X U5X8320Heavy Duty Utility Muscle The U5X Tandem Axle Utility Trailer is a 14000 lbs GVWR utility trailer made for the working man. It’s an all-around versatile trailer for construction purposes and it can haul heavy materials and equipment like mini excavators or tractors with your ¾ ton truck. The U5X deck is 20’ long and 83 inches wide and it weighs 3500 lbs so you can haul close to 10500 lbs with this trailer. Up front the U5X hooks to your vehicle with a 2 5/16” DEMCO EZ-Latch adjustable coupler mounted to a 6” channel wrap tongue and a 5” x 3” x ¼” steel angle mainframe. The treated wood floor deck is supported by 3” channel crossmembers spaced at 16” apart and a 10k drop leg jack raises and lowers the front of the trailer. This trailer has a 16” tall 3” square tubing top-rail on the front and sides of the trailer and has hooks and bullnose d-ring on the deck for easy tying down of cargo. Heavy-duty equipment standup ramps with built-in support knees make loading and unloading your equipment easy and safe. Two 7000 lb electric brake axles paired with 235/80 10-ply Radial tires carry the U5X down the road. Along with steel diamond plate fenders this trailer has clear LED running lights on the sides and in the rear bumper as well. Like all of our trailers the U5X is 100% built in Texas and is ready to get work done. We build trailers so you can dream big and work hard.

title: 2022 MAXXD N6X N6X8324 Car / Racing Trailer
description: 2022 MAXXD Trailers N6X N6X8324LOOKS GOOD. HAULS BETTER. If you’re ready to turn heads at the track and have a reliable workhorse car hauler all in one package look no further than the N6X car hauling trailer. It’s packed with the features experienced users demand and showcases high-end aluminum trim and ultra-functional running boards. From the very start the N6X car hauler is a performance trailer. And while it excels at hauling performance vehicles it’s no slouch when it comes to the day-to-day grind. It’s the perfect blend of form and function. We build the N6X car hauler on a heavy duty tube-style frame with angled front corners on the deck. This design allows the tongue to wrap back into the frame underneath the trailer floor. This style not only looks great but significantly increases overall strength as well. The 3” crossmembers are spaced on 16” centers and in-floor tie downs create a sleek overall look while providing enough hardpoints to secure your vehicles. The back end of the N6X car hauler features a 4’ dovetail for a reduced loading angle. Combined with the wide 72”x22” tubing steel ramps this dovetail makes loading even the lowest of vehicles a breeze. The dovetail also features the same rugged diamond tread plate flooring as the rest of the trailer for a slip resistant durable surface. The N6X is configured to shine as a car hauling trailer at the track and elsewhere but we didn’t forget about the fundamentals either. The 2 5/16” ball coupler is adjustable in height and the drop-leg jack provides convenience while hitching up. We also included thoughtful add-ons like a spare tire mount and ramp stoppers to prevent the ramps from falling out of the trailer when removing them. The N6X comes in a standard 83” width and lengths ranging from 18’ to 24’ in 2’ increments. And with a GVWR of 9990 pounds it’s the perfect size for most car hauling needs. A single electric brake axle comes standard as do tear-drop style fenders and 15” black mod wheels. Like all MAXX-D Trailers the N6X car hauler is finished with our industry-leading powder coating process. Six different steps all work together to give your trailer a premium powder coated steel surface with unmatched durability. Through our expansive dealer network we give you the option to configure your N6X car hauling trailer with a variety of special options to make your life easier. Whether it’s an aluminum rock shield in-floor toolbox or a winch plate and E-track you can get an N6X that’s perfect for whatever it is you’re hauling. We also offer the N6X in your choice of attractive color options. No matter what kind of vehicle you need to haul we’ve got an N6X in a configuration for you. Build something great with an N6X car hauler!

title: 2023 MAXXD G8X G8X10224 Equipment Trailer
description: 2023 MAXXD Trailers G8X G8X10224Heavy Duty Features Simple Operation The G8X is the split deck gravity tilting version of our best-in-class T8X powered tilt trailer. The G8X tilt deck equipment trailer offers a hydraulically dampened tilting deck with your choice of a 4’ 6’ 8’ 10’ or 12’ stationary front deck. This gives you room to load cargo up front and still have the option to haul heavier equipment like tractors skid steers recreational vehicles and SUVs or cars. Available in 22’ 24’ 26’ 28’ and 30’ total lengths the G8X tilt deck equipment trailer comes standard with two 7K Dexter torsion electric brake axles for a standard GVRW of 14000 pounds. These torsion axles provide a smoother ride and a longer warranty than comparable spring axles as well as a lower overall ride height. Combined with the mechanically simple easy-to-tilt bed these lower axles make your G8X tilt deck equipment trailer safe and easy to load. A rugged knife-edge rear deck brings the back of the trailer all the way to the ground when the bed is tilted making it ideal for loading low-clearance equipment and vehicles. The diamond-plate steel edge provides enhanced durability for this high-wear area as well. The G8X also includes bullnose D-rings and a full-length stake pocket and rub rail system for plenty of options when tying down your vehicles. Like all MAXX-D trailers the G8X tilt deck equipment trailer is finished with our industry-leading powder coating process. Six different steps all work together to give your tilt trailer a premium powder-coated steel surface with unmatched durability. Through our expansive dealer network we give you the option to configure your G8X tilt deck equipment trailer with a variety of options to fit your needs. Whether it’s an extra set of D-rings flooring style coupler configuration or your choice of jack you can get a G8X that’s perfect for whatever it is you’re building.

title: 2023 MAXXD T8X T8X10224 Equipment Trailer
description: 2023 MAXXD Trailers T8X T8X10224The Ultimate Powered Tilt Trailer The T8X powered tilt trailer is perfect for users seeking a fully-featured easy to use trailer with a full-length tilting bed. Raising and lowering the deck is as easy as activating the hydraulic power unit and letting the trailer do the work! It’s even available with a wireless remote for raising and lowering the bed from inside your tow vehicle. The T8X is perfect for hauling equipment with longer wheelbases tractors with farm implements or even two small cars. We build the T8X in 22’ 24’ 28’ and 32’. In the 22’ and 24’ lengths the T8X features dual cylinder control to keep your load balanced. Width between the fenders on a standard T8X is 83” and we offer the option of rugged drive over fenders for a full-width use of 102”. No matter which deck length you choose we designed the T8X with low loading angles for your safety and convenience. Two torsion axles come standard on the T8X powered tilt trailer providing a base GVWR of 14000 pounds. These torsion axles feature an enhanced warranty over a traditional suspension style and provide a smoother ride and lower deck height. With the right axle options specified your T8X can feature a max GVWR of 21000 pounds. Integrated steps located at the front and rear of each fender provide easy deck access to check or secure your load. These steps also house high-visibility long-lasting LED lighting. These ultra-bright LED lights are flush fitting to help prevent damage. Frames on the T8X powered tilt trailer are made from 6” x 2” x ¼” tubing with 3” channel crossmembers on 12” centers. This close crossmember spacing creates a stiff deck capable of hauling multiple vehicles or pieces of equipment. Several different flooring options are available on the T8X powered tilt trailer. From the standard treated wood floor to rough oak diamond plated steel or the revolutionary Blackwood rubber infused lumber you can get a T8X built exactly to your needs. Like all MAXX-D Trailers the T8X powered tilt trailer is finished with our industry-leading powder coating process. Six different steps all work together to give your trailer a premium powder-coated steel surface with unmatched durability. Through our expansive dealer network we give you the option to configure your T8X powered tilt trailer with a variety of special options to make your life easier. Whether it’s a winch plate and winch different floor style or hydraulic jacks you can get a T8X that’s perfect for whatever it is you’re hauling.

title: 2021 MAXXD DJX DJX8314 Dump Trailer
description: 2021 MAXXD Trailers DJX DJX8314A CONFIGURATION FOR ANY SITUATION We offer an incredible amount of variety and customization in all the dump trailers we offer but the DJX takes it up a notch. It’s equally at home hauling loose brush loads or heavy equipment. Based on an 8” I-beam frame the DJX includes heavy-duty features like an industry-leading 6” scissor hoist. We house the KTI hydraulic pump and Interstate battery in a unique full-width internally split toolbox. This protects the heart of the hydraulics system and provides a convenient place for chains and other important tools. You can also choose to outfit the DJX with 2’ 3’ or 4’ tall Tuff Sides. These sides provide a massive 3” top cap surface that wraps partially down the side of the trailer. These top rails are then supported with flared steel side supports. Combined they help form a bed that’s extremely resistant to warping dents and damage. All of our dumps come equipped with tarp-kits as a standard feature. We build each DJX with a standard GVWR of 14000 lbs and twin 7K Dexter electric brake axles. You can configure these versatile dumps in lengths of 12’ 14' and 16' with base weights ranging from 4150 lbs to 4550 lbs. Like all Maxxd Trailers the DJX I-beam dump model is finished with our industry-leading powder coating process. Six different steps all work together to give your trailer a premium powder-coated steel surface with unmatched durability. Through our expansive dealer network we give you the option to configure your DJX low profile dump trailer with a variety of options to fit your needs. Whether it’s an extra set of D-rings solar battery charger or your choice of side height and configuration you can get a DJX that’s perfect for whatever it is you’re building. With both gooseneck and bumper pull styles available the DJX is an ideal choice for construction roofing agriculture landscaping and any other large projects you can dream of. Build something great with a DJX I-beam dump trailer!

title: 2021 MAXXD DTX DTX8316 Other
description: 2021 MAXXD Trailers DTX DTX8316Maximum Dumping Leverage We offer an incredible amount of variety and customization in all the dump trailers we offer but the DTX takes it up a notch. It’s equally at home hauling loose brush loads or heavy equipment. Based on an 8” I-beam frame the DTX features a heavy-duty direct-push telescoping cylinder. The direct-push cylinder design puts less stress on the trailer and easier tilting of the dump bed. We house the KTI hydraulic pump and Interstate battery in a unique full-width internally split toolbox. This protects the heart of the hydraulics system and provides a convenient place for chains and other important tools. You can also choose to outfit the DTX with 4’ tall Tuff Sides but not 2’ sides. These sides provide a massive 3” top cap surface that wraps partially down the side of the trailer. These top rails are then supported with flared steel side supports. Combined they help form a bed that’s extremely resistant to warping dents and damage. All of our dumps come equipped with tarp-kits as a standard feature. Like all MAXX-D Trailers the DTX I-beam dump model is finished with our industry-leading powder coating process. Six different steps all work together to give your trailer a premium powder-coated steel surface with unmatched durability. Through our expansive dealer network we give you the option to configure your DTX low profile dump trailer with a variety of options to fit your needs. Whether it’s an extra set of D-rings solar battery charger or your choice of side height and configuration you can get a DTX that’s perfect for whatever it is you’re building. With both gooseneck and bumper pull styles available the DTX is an ideal choice for construction roofing agriculture landscaping and any other large projects you can dream of. Build something great with a DTX I-beam dump trailer! We build each DTX with a standard GVWR of 14000 lbs and twin 7K Dexter electric brake axles. You can configure these versatile dumps in lengths of 12’ 14' and 16' with base weights ranging from 4750 lbs to 5150 lbs.

title: 2023 MAXXD A6X A6X8024 Car / Racing Trailer
description: 2023 MAXXD Trailers A6X A6X8024 The Next Generation Of Car Trailer Finally an answer to the age-old dilemma of loading ultra-low sports cars and specialty vehicles. We took the concept of an air-bagged car suspension system and applied it to a car hauling trailer. The result is an incredibly easy to use trailer that loads even the lowest of vehicles with ease: The MAXX-D DROP-N-LOAD® car trailer. The knife-edge tail on a MAXX-D Drop-N-Load comes right down to ground level and gives the entire deck an industry-leading load angle. At the front of the trailer we install a tall diamond-plated rock shield to protect your valuable cars from road debris. Base weights start at 3300 pounds and we offer the DROP-N-LOAD® in 20’ and 24’ lengths. While we designed the DROP-N-LOAD® A6X with sleek styling and accents that highlight the lines of performance vehicles. this trailer isn’t just for race cars. The low deck angle eliminates the need for ramps making loading any car truck or SUV much safer and more convenient. And while there is a definite component of the DROP-N-LOAD® that is built for show there’s still plenty of “go” underneath the front-mounted toolbox. Dual Interstate batteries and rugged pneumatics mean the A6X DROP-N-LOAD® will be working hard for years to come. Like all MAXX-D Trailers the A6X DROP-N-LOAD® is finished with our industry-leading powder coating process. Six different steps all work together to give your flatbed trailer a premium powder-coated steel surface with unmatched durability and your choice of nine different colors. Through our expansive dealer network we give you the choice to configure your A6X DROP-N-LOAD trailer with a variety of options to fit your needs. Whether it’s an in-floor toolbox full-length E-track for tying down or a Warrior winch you can get an A6X DROP-N-LOAD® trailer package that’s perfect for your needs. You’ll ask yourself how you ever got along without the safety convenience and features provided by the A6X Drop-N-Load trailer. Do something great with a MAXX-D Drop-N-Load trailer!
